    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-11T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-11T23:00:00-05:00" n="575"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/9555: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-12T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >October 12, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1165. Department’s 854, September 22, 5 p.m. Kunming Consulate reports that,
                    until new cargo plane field at Yanglin near Kunming is completed towards end of
                    year, there does not appear to be much likelihood that available plane space
                    will exceed cargo. Beginning next year it may be advisable to devise means to
                    encourage increased deliveries of wolfram.</p>
                <p>United States Army headquarters here has informed Embassy of temporary
                    interruption of shipment of strategic materials to provide for transfer of
                    Chinese troops to India by air.</p>
                <p>Department’s 879, September 28, 6 p.m.,<note n="34" xml:id="d575fn34">Not
                        printed.</note> last paragraph. All available air space now being utilized
                    as far as is known.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
